                In <expan><abbr>h</abbr><ex>onorem</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>omus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>ivinae</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>de</abbr><ex>ae</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Epon</abbr><ex>ae</ex></expan> Bilic<supplied reason="lost">i</supplied><lb break="no" n="2"/>us Gematus col<expan><ex>l</ex><abbr>eg</abbr><ex>i</ex><abbr>s</abbr></expan> su<supplied reason="lost">i</supplied><lb break="no" n="3"/>s de iu&amp;lt;s=C&amp;gt;(su) <expan><abbr>de</abbr><ex>ae</ex></expan> &amp;lt;I=T&amp;gt;<supplied reason="lost">m</supplied>&amp;lt;p=I<certainty match="preceding-sibling::node()" locus="value"/>&amp;gt;(eratore) <supplied reason="lost">C</supplied>a&amp;lt;e=I&amp;gt;<expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>are</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>ucio</ex></expan> Sep<supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>t</abbr><ex>imio</ex></expan></supplied> <lb n="4"/><supplied reason="lost">Severo</supplied> A&amp;lt;ra=IM&amp;gt;<supplied reason="lost">bi</supplied>&amp;lt;c=S&amp;gt;o Adia<supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>b</abbr><ex>enico</ex></expan></supplied> <lb n="5"/><supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>Parth</abbr><ex>ico</ex></expan> ma</supplied>xi<supplied reason="lost">mo c</supplied>o<expan><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ule</ex></expan> II<supplied reason="lost">I</supplied> <lb n="0"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/> 
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Die Inschrift befindet sich unterhalb einer Reliefdarstellung der Epona; zahlreiche Fragmente; stark ergänzt; Maße inklusive Ergänzungen. Reste von roter Farbe in den Buchstaben. Z. 3: vom &amp;quot;&amp;quot;P&amp;quot;&amp;quot; in Imp(erator) nur das obere Ende einer senkrechten Haste, wohl eines I, erhalten. (B): Jacobi, Limes 6, 27; AE 1898; Jacobi, Limes 7, 34; AE 1902; CIL 13, 07438; Jacobi, in: Der obergermanisch-rätische Limes; Espérandieu; Mattern: Lesung abweichend / unvollständig.</p>
            </div>
